          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "LEAST",
                "INTAD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The  least-square  method   for   (g,p)",
                " reaction  differential  cross section obtaining from",
                " (e,e'p) reaction cross sections measured  using  the",
                " direct   proton   detection   with   the   following",
                " integration over angles."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Root-mean-squared errors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The reaction 142Nd(e,e'p)141Pr has been used to study",
                " the T> giant resonance in 142Nd.  Cross sections for",
                " the 142Nd(g,p)141Pr     and      142Nd(g,p0+p1)141Pr",
                " reactions were measured for excitation energies from",
                " 15.9 to 26.0 MeV.  These cross sections are compared",
                " with the   previous   141Pr(p,g-0)142Nd   data.  The",
                " angular distributions for the larger  resonances  at",
                " 17.3, 19.7,  and  22.9  MeV were measured.  Analysis",
                " indicates that 22.9 MeV state has about a  13  %  E2",
                " component. The  decay  proton  spectra from the 19.7",
                " and 22.9 MeV  resonances  were  analyzed   with   a",
                " schematic shell  model  and  indicates that the core",
                " excitation process is  dominant  in  these  isobaric",
                " analog resonances.  The measured (g,p) cross section",
                " together with the (g,n) cross section is found to be",
                " fairly consistent  with  the  predictions of isospin",
                " splitting theory."
              ]
            }
          ],
